.NET 10's `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` upgrades from **Microsoft.OpenApi v1** to **v2**, which aligns with OpenAPI 3.1 / JSON Schema. Here are the breaking changes in your code and the fixes:

---

**① `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` removed — use `System.Text.Json.Nodes`**

`OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc. are gone. `Schema.Example` is now `JsonNode?`.

```csharp
// OLD
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// NEW
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

---

**② `Schema.Nullable` removed — use `JsonSchemaType` flags**

OpenAPI 3.1 represents nullability as a type flag, not a separate boolean.

```csharp
// OLD
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// NEW
if (property.Value.Type.HasValue)
    property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

---

**③ `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` key changed to `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference`**

The dictionary key is now `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference` (not `OpenApiSecurityScheme` with a `Reference` property), and the value is `List<string>` (not `IList<string>`).

```csharp
// OLD
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
};
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
};

// NEW
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2", context.Document);
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes.ToList() }
};
```

> `context.Document` is available on operation/schema transformer contexts in .NET 10.

---

**④ `Responses.TryAdd` — no change needed**

`operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { ... })` still works.

---

### Full corrected code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2", context.Document);
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes.ToList() }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true
                && property.Value.Type.HasValue)
            {
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
            }
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```
